MONGO / SCRAPING NOTES

////// TO START MONGODB \\\\\
https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-windows/

To Run MongoDB
"C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\3.4\bin\mongod.exe"
((Must have the quotation marks))
To Connect to MongoDB
"C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\3.4\bin\mongo.exe"

- Start up a new database by switching to it.
-- NOTE: The db does not exist until you create a collection.

- For sorting entries, type this into the cl
"db.collection.find().sort({field_name:1})"
-- NOTE: the 1 is for acending results; -1 is for decending


db.collection.update(
   {'source':'Vigilant Citizen'},
   {'image':'',
   {
     upsert: <boolean>,
     multi: <boolean>,
     writeConcern: <document>
   }
)
